Defendant in custody.
The State moves to delete both enhancers.  Motion granted.
NO CONTEST plea entered to the amended charge of deliver heroin.  Convicted.
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of three (3) years.  That is eighteen (18) months initial confinement followed by eighteen (18) months extended supervision.
The court finds the defendant eligible for both the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) Pay court costs including $100.00 buy money to Metro Drug Unit;
2) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
3) provide DNA sample and pay the surcharge;
4) maintain absolute sobriety;
5) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
6) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
7) Defendant is to use only one doctor and one pharmacist for obtaining and filing prescriptions;
8) Defendant is to have no association with any known drug dealers or users.
The defendant has credit for 2 days.
Minutes.
